1:42:10.207 --> 1:42:13.167
the last year and a half
of my life investigating...

1:42:13.252 --> 1:42:18.005
Innocent civilians are
really little more than
disposable lives,

1:42:18.090 --> 1:42:21.634
thought of as
collateral damage.

1:42:23.053 --> 1:42:26.305
And I believe it was
simply the public nature
of my position that

1:42:28.142 --> 1:42:30.518
saved me
from a similar fate.

1:42:33.647 --> 1:42:38.734
So, as political suicides go,

1:42:40.028 --> 1:42:41.737
how was that?

1:42:50.330 --> 1:42:52.123
CAMERON:
Thank you, Congressman.

1:43:06.346 --> 1:43:08.055
You okay?
Yeah.

1:43:08.515 --> 1:43:10.016
He was set up.

1:43:11.852 --> 1:43:15.855
She was sleeping with him
for $26,000 a month. I mean...

1:43:19.401 --> 1:43:20.568
Sliberty.

1:43:20.652 --> 1:43:21.861
Cal.

1:43:24.573 --> 1:43:26.657
You all set?
Okay.
Mmm-Hmm.

1:43:27.743 --> 1:43:29.035
Let's go.

1:43:40.881 --> 1:43:42.215
(SIGHS)

1:43:50.599 --> 1:43:53.351
You still here?
Yeah.

1:43:53.435 --> 1:43:57.313
I thought you would've been
down at your desk
blasting it online.

1:43:57.522 --> 1:43:59.398
Well, you know,
a piece this big,

1:43:59.483 --> 1:44:00.733
people should
probably have newsprint

1:44:00.817 --> 1:44:02.193
on their hands
when they read it,

1:44:02.277 --> 1:44:03.861
don't you think?

1:44:05.781 --> 1:44:08.824
I'll do Collins,
Fergus, PointCorp,

1:44:08.909 --> 1:44:10.326
and corporate and
government malfeasance.

1:44:10.410 --> 1:44:12.078
Okay.
You do Sonia Baker...

1:44:12.162 --> 1:44:15.373
The murder, Mandi,
Rhonda Silver.

1:44:15.832 --> 1:44:18.376
And the Dominic Foy
connection, all right?
Yeah.

1:44:18.502 --> 1:44:20.169
Retire to the
neutral corner.
Okay.

1:44:20.254 --> 1:44:22.004
Gentle. Thank you.

1:44:31.640 --> 1:44:33.557
Sir, it's Robert Bingham.

1:44:33.684 --> 1:44:35.643
I'm sorry to
call you directly.

1:44:36.186 --> 1:44:39.480
I want to assure you
that I'm ready to finish
what we started.

1:44:41.024 --> 1:44:42.108
Goodbye.

1:45:10.220 --> 1:45:12.096
(GARBAGE DISPOSAL GRINDING)

1:45:54.973 --> 1:45:57.224
I won't be
more than an hour.

1:46:04.066 --> 1:46:06.192
Hey, guys.
Evening, sir.
How you doing?

1:46:15.285 --> 1:46:16.619
(TAPPING)

1:46:18.455 --> 1:46:20.414
Hello.
CAL: Is it a night for it?

1:46:21.416 --> 1:46:25.044
Yeah, yeah,
I think it is.

1:46:33.220 --> 1:46:36.472
So, how old are you?
Actually, don't tell me.

1:46:36.556 --> 1:46:38.099
It would just
make me sick.

1:46:38.183 --> 1:46:39.850
You never ask
a girl her age.

1:46:40.352 --> 1:46:43.396
Well, see, I look at you,
and I don't see a girl.
I just see a reporter.

1:46:43.480 --> 1:46:45.981
(SIGHS) At last.
Anyway, back to the story.

1:46:46.191 --> 1:46:47.191
Yes.

1:46:48.026 --> 1:46:50.486
So I had this, uh, English
teacher in high school.
Mmm-hmm.

1:46:50.570 --> 1:46:54.782
He was a kind of a longhaired
hippie kind of guy.
Mmm-hmm.

1:46:55.367 --> 1:46:57.993
He had
a pen problem. Yeah.
Oh.

1:46:58.495 --> 1:47:00.329
He solved it by
having a piece

1:47:00.497 --> 1:47:02.289
of leather string
around his neck,

1:47:02.374 --> 1:47:03.833
and that's where
he'd keep his pen.

1:47:04.292 --> 1:47:05.543
Smart.

1:47:05.669 --> 1:47:07.461
So I started thinking,

1:47:07.546 --> 1:47:10.131
"My friend Della's
got a pen problem.

1:47:10.298 --> 1:47:12.383
(EXCLAIMS)
"How do I solve it?"

1:47:12.509 --> 1:47:14.427
And I came up
with this.
What is it?

1:47:14.511 --> 1:47:17.805
I call it the "Della
Frye Nubian Princess,

1:47:17.931 --> 1:47:21.267
"'I'm never without a pen"'
celebratory necklace.

1:47:21.351 --> 1:47:25.187
Oh, it's beautiful!
I always wanted one
of these.

1:47:29.901 --> 1:47:31.735
Cheers.
Cheers.

1:47:35.449 --> 1:47:39.368
You know, I wanted
to tell you something
about Anne Collins.

1:47:40.287 --> 1:47:41.579
Okay.

1:47:59.055 --> 1:48:01.056
I was just talking to her.

1:48:05.187 --> 1:48:06.187
How does Anne
Collins know that

1:48:06.271 --> 1:48:08.355
Sonia Baker was
earning $26,000 a month?

1:48:11.485 --> 1:48:12.568
What?

1:48:15.113 --> 1:48:17.031
How does she know
how much Sonia Baker
was earning?

1:48:17.115 --> 1:48:18.491
We know that.
Yeah.

1:48:18.575 --> 1:48:20.242
How does Anne
Collins know that?

1:48:20.327 --> 1:48:25.498
Well, I mean, Stephen
must have heard it
in the Foy interview.

1:48:26.416 --> 1:48:28.792
We played him
a specific part
of that tape,

1:48:28.919 --> 1:48:31.295
and that figure
is never mentioned.

1:48:49.523 --> 1:48:52.608
Cal. Wait,
what are you doing?

1:49:03.870 --> 1:49:06.789
DELLA: What are
you doing? Cal?

1:49:13.088 --> 1:49:14.380
You gonna fill me in?

1:49:14.464 --> 1:49:16.340
Just tell Cameron,
"Hold the story."

1:49:17.968 --> 1:49:22.304
What? Cal? Cal!

1:49:25.934 --> 1:49:27.101
Shit.

1:49:52.502 --> 1:49:54.712
Who's Robert Bingham,
Stephen?

1:50:06.641 --> 1:50:08.642
Who is Robert Bingham?

1:50:15.692 --> 1:50:17.276
(SIGHS)

1:50:27.245 --> 1:50:29.121
Are the police outside?

1:50:30.665 --> 1:50:32.041
No.

1:50:34.377 --> 1:50:37.546
I saved Robert Bingham's
life in Kuwait in '91.

1:50:38.548 --> 1:50:40.799
He was a 17-year-old kid.

1:50:40.925 --> 1:50:43.135
He was a good soldier.

1:50:43.219 --> 1:50:45.387
He was proud
of what we did.

1:50:46.222 --> 1:50:51.268
The Army was his life,
and he had problems
when he got discharged.

1:50:51.394 --> 1:50:54.313
So you had a guy that
you knew to be unstable

1:50:55.607 --> 1:50:58.651
do what, exactly?
Scare her?

1:50:58.735 --> 1:51:00.027
Maybe beat her up
a little?

1:51:00.111 --> 1:51:02.780
No, Cal.
I had him follow her.

1:51:03.198 --> 1:51:04.156
Why?

1:51:04.240 --> 1:51:07.368
Because I knew
she was hiding
something from me.

1:51:08.536 --> 1:51:09.828
Because when I'd...
I'd be at her house

1:51:09.913 --> 1:51:11.664
and a fax would come in,
she'd get nervous.

1:51:11.748 --> 1:51:14.333
Because there were
phone calls late at night.

1:51:14.417 --> 1:51:16.168
I was suspicious.

1:51:16.252 --> 1:51:19.963
I asked Bingham
to observe her
and report back to me.

1:51:20.048 --> 1:51:22.132
That's all.

1:51:23.510 --> 1:51:24.635
You're a liar, Stephen.

1:51:24.719 --> 1:51:27.471
He was more upset
about what she was
doing than I was.

1:51:27.555 --> 1:51:29.807
You have to understand
what the military
means to Bingham.

1:51:29.891 --> 1:51:32.351
He hates PointCorp
for what they're
trying to do to it.

1:51:32.435 --> 1:51:33.811
In his mind,
she just had to stop.

1:51:33.937 --> 1:51:35.354
But she did stop,
right?

1:51:35.438 --> 1:51:37.856
She tore up her paychecks,
and she put her life
at risk for you.

1:51:37.941 --> 1:51:40.067
Yes, but I didn't
know that.

1:51:40.360 --> 1:51:43.112
I didn't know that
he was gonna kill her.

1:51:43.655 --> 1:51:45.364
I didn't know
he had killed her.

1:51:45.448 --> 1:51:47.366
When I found out,
my thought was just
the same as yours.

1:51:47.450 --> 1:51:49.284
I thought PointCorp
had done it.

1:51:49.369 --> 1:51:50.369
And when you did
find out?

1:51:50.453 --> 1:51:51.412
What was
I supposed to do?

1:51:51.496 --> 1:51:53.163
Tell someone.
I tried.

1:51:53.248 --> 1:51:54.373
When?
When I came
to your house,

1:51:54.457 --> 1:51:55.666
and I wanted to
talk to you about it,

1:51:55.792 --> 1:51:56.834
and all you cared
about was the story.

1:51:56.918 --> 1:51:59.503
No, Stephen,
I cared about helping you.

1:51:59.587 --> 1:52:01.463
Bullshit. Bullshit.

1:52:01.548 --> 1:52:04.174
All you cared about was
clearing your conscience
over this little soap opera

1:52:04.259 --> 1:52:05.968
you have with Annie.
So you used me.

1:52:06.094 --> 1:52:07.428
No, Cal.
The same way
as you used Bingham.

1:52:07.512 --> 1:52:09.388
I was suspicious of her.
I brought him in.

1:52:09.514 --> 1:52:11.432
That's all it was!
It was a mistake!

1:52:11.516 --> 1:52:12.641
It's my responsibility.

1:52:12.809 --> 1:52:13.934
I should never
have done that.

1:52:14.018 --> 1:52:16.145
But I never asked
him to kill her.

1:52:16.312 --> 1:52:18.439
He owed you his life!

1:52:20.400 --> 1:52:22.401
That's why
you called him.

1:52:23.153 --> 1:52:25.446
You called him,
and you used him,

1:52:26.281 --> 1:52:28.699
like you've been
trying to use me.

1:52:29.325 --> 1:52:32.578
One to kill,
and one to cover it up.

1:52:32.829 --> 1:52:34.329
If PointCorp and
Fergus hadn't hired her,

1:52:34.456 --> 1:52:36.540
none of this
would've happened!
No. This is not about Bingham

1:52:36.624 --> 1:52:38.417
and PointCorp
and Fergus, man!

1:52:38.501 --> 1:52:42.045
It's about you
and the decisions
that you have made

1:52:42.130 --> 1:52:44.506
that have led to four
people being killed.

1:52:45.842 --> 1:52:48.802
One of them was
delivering a pizza,
Stephen.

1:52:50.680 --> 1:52:54.349
Cal. What are
you gonna do?

1:52:55.560 --> 1:52:57.686
You know
what I'm gonna do.

1:53:00.273 --> 1:53:05.194
You know, it's laughable,
your sense of
your own self-worth.

1:53:06.613 --> 1:53:08.739
Why is that?
'Cause nobody reads
the papers anymore?

1:53:08.823 --> 1:53:10.616
Is that it?

1:53:10.825 --> 1:53:13.327
It's just another story,
a couple days of shitstorm,

1:53:13.411 --> 1:53:15.162
and it's wrapping paper?

1:53:15.246 --> 1:53:17.247
You know, in the middle
of all this gossip
and speculation

1:53:17.332 --> 1:53:18.457
that permeates
people's lives,

1:53:18.541 --> 1:53:20.083
I still think
they know the difference

1:53:20.168 --> 1:53:22.044
between real news
and bullshit.

1:53:22.462 --> 1:53:25.130
And they're glad that
someone cares enough

1:53:25.215 --> 1:53:27.633
to get things on the record
and print the truth.

1:53:27.717 --> 1:53:30.969
Cal. Please,
Cal, don't do this.
Please.

1:53:31.054 --> 1:53:33.263
I'm asking you
as your friend.

1:53:35.892 --> 1:53:39.269
You got about three minutes
before the cops get here.

1:53:41.564 --> 1:53:44.274
I thought you said
you didn't call them.

1:53:45.568 --> 1:53:46.735
I lied.

1:54:22.564 --> 1:54:24.106
(KEYS RATTLING)

1:54:26.526 --> 1:54:27.901
(GUN COCKING)

1:54:35.493 --> 1:54:39.329
A good soldier fights
for his country
and his friends.

1:54:39.414 --> 1:54:41.039
(SIRENS WAILING)

1:54:41.291 --> 1:54:44.710
But these guys,
they want to make it
all about the money.

1:54:47.547 --> 1:54:49.006
You want to live
in a world like that?

1:54:49.090 --> 1:54:50.632
DONALD: Drop the weapon!

1:54:51.301 --> 1:54:53.969
The story about
Stephen comes out,
whether I write it or not.

1:54:54.053 --> 1:54:55.262
COP 1: Drop your weapon!

1:54:55.555 --> 1:54:56.722
COP 2: Drop it!

1:54:57.307 --> 1:54:58.891
I'd rather be nothing.

1:54:58.975 --> 1:55:01.310
COP 1: I repeat,
drop your weapon!

1:55:03.646 --> 1:55:05.188
(GUNS FIRING)

1:56:14.050 --> 1:56:15.550
(SIGHS)

1:57:05.101 --> 1:57:07.853
CAMERON: Well, aren't
you gonna send it?

1:57:08.146 --> 1:57:12.107
I've only been holding
the front page
for four hours, after all.

1:57:12.817 --> 1:57:14.234
You send it.

1:57:19.407 --> 1:57:21.575
Good night, everybody.
See you tomorrow.

1:57:27.040 --> 1:57:29.207
Yinzer.

1:58:02.492 --> 1:58:05.160
(LONG AS I CAN SEE
THE LIGHT PLAYING)

1:58:18.174 --> 1:58:21.676
(MAN SINGING)
Put a candle in the window

1:58:25.932 --> 1:58:30.352
'Cause I feel I've got to move

1:58:33.481 --> 1:58:36.942
Though I'm going, going

1:58:37.026 --> 1:58:39.653
I'll be coming home soon

1:58:40.738 --> 1:58:44.449
Long as I can see the light

1:58:48.246 --> 1:58:52.374
Pack my bag
and let's get movin'

1:58:56.087 --> 1:59:00.340
'Cause I'm bound
to drift a while

1:59:03.511 --> 1:59:07.013
When I'm gone, gone

1:59:07.181 --> 1:59:09.766
You don't have to worry long

1:59:10.768 --> 1:59:15.021
Long as I can see the light

1:59:18.276 --> 1:59:22.154
Guess I've got
that old travlin' bone

1:59:26.200 --> 1:59:30.745
'Cause this feelin'
won't leave me alone

1:59:33.749 --> 1:59:37.252
But I won't, won't

1:59:37.587 --> 1:59:40.338
Be losing my way, no, no

1:59:41.048 --> 1:59:44.885
Long as I can see the light

1:59:48.598 --> 1:59:57.647
Yeah

1:59:59.108 --> 2:00:00.650
Oh, yeah

2:00:03.362 --> 2:00:07.115
Put a candle in the window

2:00:11.245 --> 2:00:15.123
'Cause I feel I've got to move

2:00:18.794 --> 2:00:22.255
Though I'm going, going

2:00:22.465 --> 2:00:24.841
I'll be coming home soon

